        "category": "ancestry",
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You're well versed in using the subtle art of body language to convey the basics of your intentions, even when you don't share a language with whom you're attempting to communicate. You can use Diplomacy to [[/act make-an-impression]] without a shared language with your target. When you do, Make an Impression loses the auditory and linguistic traits, and you can attempt the Diplomacy check with a –2 circumstance penalty. When you do share at least one language with your target, you instead gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Make an Impression.</p>"
        },
